tags: That glance I keep talking about
I hadn't seen anyone screencap this bit so I did
summary: Coordinated Portaling! Whenever I chat about how awesome Stephen and Wong’s friendship is I always talk this moment. They had to...
caption:
Coordinated Portaling!

Whenever I chat about how awesome Stephen and Wong’s friendship is I always talk this moment. They had to have practiced this. There are two ways they could be thinking with portals here. What I assume is happening is that they have a set location somewhere remote. When they do this move the spikes go in Stephen’s portal to the location, and then it lines up perfectly with Wong’s portal sending the items back.

The reason why I screencapped two moments is because I love Stephen glancing over at Wong, checking to make sure they are in sync. Since Wong has been portalling a lot longer, chances are good this is a strat Wong taught him.

It’s a short scene, but very well done. It has tactics, friendship and it shows a bit about what they are up to between movies

summary: Fancast for the possible “Hawkeye” streaming show (main cast only)
title: Fancast for the possible “Hawkeye” streaming show (main cast only)
body:
1) Jeremy Renner as Clint Barton / Hawkeye

2) Katherine Langford as Kate Bishop / Hawkeye II (in keeping with the rumor mill)

3) Aidan Gillen as Barney Barton / Trickshot II (main villain)

4) Adrianne Palicki as Bobbi Morse / Mockingbird (ex-girlfriend, now Clint and Kate’s employer, in reference to the comics) 

5) Linda Cardellini as Laura Barton 

6) Jimmy Smits as Buck Chisholm (the original Trickshot and Clint’s mentor / father figure)

7) Gaspard Ulliel as Jacques Duquesne / Swordsman (Clint’s former rival-turned-reluctant ally) 

8) Devery Jacobs as Maya Lopez / Echo / Ronin (another one of Clint’s allies, who adopts the “Ronin” alias after Clint used it in Infinity War) 

9) Andy Samberg as an original character who befriends both Clint and Kate. He acts as their “guy in chair” / comic relief sidekick who is killed by Barney near the end of the season. In his will, he leaves his dog, Lucky, to Clint and Kate. Like Lucky, he enjoyed eating pizza, which becomes a recurring joke in the series.
